Hi So I'm a Dispensing Optician, you'll find your eyes get blurrier when you're using screens as it reduces your blink reflex. SO you blink less, and eyes get dry and blurr vision. It's important to use the 20-20-20 rule. Every 20mins, look 20meters away for 20 seconds. This lets your eyes re-adjust and stops any strain or potential headaches due to accommodative strain. :)
